Decision theory:

Clarify the problem at hand: We need to know problem are we trying to solve
List the possible alternatives: We need too know all the alteratives to solving our problem
Identify the possible outcomes: We nee to know the possible outcomes of each of the alternatives
List the payoff or profit of each combination of alternatives and outcomes: Listing the payoffs of each combination will give us a better opinion of how to solve our problem.
Select a mathematicial decision theory model: Select the best decision theory for our problem.
Apply the model and make a decision: apply that theory to come up with the best decision.
